<dl id="n12005c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12005c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12005c"> 5(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> M<sup>hir</sup> left by Satan when / building S. Michel ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">dans nos l&eacute;gendes, son nom <font color="green">[Satan]</font> est au moins quatre-vingt-dix fois sur cent associ&eacute; au Mont St-Michel. Nos anc&ecirc;tres ont &eacute;t&eacute; tellement impressionn&eacute;s par la masse imposante, par l&apos;incomparable et quasi surhumaine magnificence de notre merveille de l&apos;occident, que, sans h&eacute;siter <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> ils en ont attribu&eacute; la construction &agrave; Satan lui-m&ecirc;me. <br><font color="green">[&hellip; in our legends, his name [Satan]</font> is almost always associated with Mont St-Michel. Our ancestors were so awed by its imposing bulk, by the incomparable and superhuman magnificence of our marvel of the Western World, that, without hesitation <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> they attributed its construction to Satan himself.] <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 15</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
